{
  "name": "Gak's Repeating Rifle",
  "type": "weapon",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><strong>Range. Loud.</strong> <strong>Ammunition. Two-handed.</strong></p><p><strong>Reload.</strong> This weapon can be fired a number of times equal to its reload score before it must be reloaded before it can be fired again. Reloading takes an action or bonus action. You must have a free hand to reload a firearm.</p><div id=\"message-content-1278730849990475867\" class=\"markup_f8f345 messageContent_f9f2ca\"><p><span><strong>Threaded Barrel.</strong> You can attach muzzle devices to this weapon.</span></p><p><span><strong>Flash Hider.</strong> When you are hidden and miss with a ranged weapon attack using this weapon, making the attack doesn‚Äôt give away your location. (but it's still loud)</span></p></div><p><strong>Big Badaboom. </strong>While tinkering with your rifle, you accidentally made some unanticipated adjustments. When you roll a 1 on an attack with this weapon, you and all creatures within 5 feet of you take [[/damage 1d4 sonic]] damage and are deafened until the start of your next turn.</p></div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
